<p>

Uday has mostly done films under his father's production house. He starred in 2004 in the action thriller <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../869/1828869.xml">
Dhoom</link></movie>
</it> and starred in its sequel <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../427/2513427.xml">
Dhoom 2</link></movie>
</it>, released in 2006. Together with his brother Aditya Chopra, Uday helps to run Yashraj Productions, and plays a major role in the Information Technology and digital rights management of the company.</p>
<p>

Before making his debut in Mohabbatein in 2000, Uday produced Yeh Dillagi (1994) starring Akshay Kumar, Kajol and Saif Ali Khan.
It was directed by Naresh Malhotra.</p>
<p>

Recently it was reported that Uday Chopra will go into directing films like his father and brother however there has been no official confirmation of this,</p>

<ss1>
<st>
 Personal life </st>
<p>

Uday started dating Tanisha in 2005, whom he met on the sets of <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../842/3212842.xml">
Neal N Nikki</link>. In 2007 they broke up.  
Both Aditya Chopra and Uday Chopra stayed at Girnar Apartments in Pali Hill, Bandra, Mumbai till the early 1980s before moving out to Juhu.</p>

